        "price": null,
        "description": "<p data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><strong>Celebrate Singapore’s rich culture through clay!</strong><br />\r\nIn this hands-on workshop, you’ll learn how to throw and paint your own kopi-style cup with iconic local themes - from hawker delights to nostalgic batik patterns. Each participant will create <strong>one cup and decorate it with a Singapore-inspired painting</strong>, such as <em>kaya toast and kopi motifs, Peranakan tile designs, old-school biscuit tins, etc</em>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPerfect for beginners and a great bonding activity for families, couples, or friends. Come create a piece of functional art filled with stories and heart.</p>",
