        "category": null,
        "price": null,
        "description": "<p><strong>About the Workshop</strong><br>Discover the basics of linocut printmaking in this fun, hands-on session. You’ll learn how to transfer a design, carve safely, and print bold, graphic images using simple tools and ink. Everyone will create their own A6 linocut block and set of prints to take home - perfect for beginners who enjoy creativity with a tactile twist.</p><ul><li>This is a beginner-friendly guided session; no prior art experience is required!&nbsp;</li><li>All workshop art materials will be provided.</li><li>Complimentary drinks are available at our studio: packet drinks, bottled water, and instant tea or coffee.</li></ul><p><br><strong>Workshop Duration:&nbsp;</strong>3 hours<br><br><strong>About Artify Studio</strong><br>Established in 2014, Artify Studio offers a range of art services from children and adult art classes, corporate team-building sessions to community outreach programmes.<br><br><strong>Venue Information&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Only lifts 7 or 8 provide access to our studio. Please press the \"12/13\" button.</li><li>Parking is available within the building.</li><li>Nearest MRT - Nicoll Highway (CC 5) / Lavender (EW 11)</li><li>Nearby buses - 107, 961, 980 (Jalan Sultan); 7, 32, 51, 61, 63, 80, 145,175, 197 (North Bridge Road), 100, 961, 980 (Beach Road)</li></ul>",
