        "description": "<p><strong>About the Workshop</strong><br />The Palette Knife Painting Experience is a beginner-friendly workshop where participants will explore texture, colour, and layering with a palette knife in a simple, approachable way. With step-by-step guidance, you will learn how to apply, blend and build paint with the knife to create bold, textured effects. Each participant will complete one textured palette knife painting on a 24 x 30 cm canvas. All materials are provided.<br /><br /><em>Theme options include:</em></p><ul><li><p>Abstract landscapes</p></li><li><p>Florals</p></li><li><p>Sunset skies</p></li><li><p>Ocean-inspired textures</p></li></ul><p>There are also <em>hundreds of palette knife reference images</em> available in the studio for inspiration. Participants are welcome to bring their own reference image, though not all images may be suitable. You can check with the instructor on the day to see if your image is achievable :)<br /><br /><strong>Workshop Duration: </strong>2.5 Hours<br /><br /><strong>About Artify Studio</strong><br />Established in 2014, Artify Studio offers a range of art services from children and adult art classes, corporate team-building sessions to community outreach programmes.<br /><br /><strong>Venue Information </strong></p><ul><li><p>Only lifts 7 or 8 provide access to our studio. Please press the\"12/13\"button.</p></li><li><p>Parking is available within the building.</p></li><li><p>Nearest MRT - Nicoll Highway (CC 5) / Lavender (EW 11)</p></li><li><p>Nearby buses - 107, 961, 980 (Jalan Sultan); 7, 32, 51, 61, 63, 80, 145,175, 197 (North Bridge Road), 100, 961, 980 (Beach Road)</p></li></ul>",
