        "price": null,
        "description": "<p><strong>Kueh Clay Accessories Workshop</strong><br />Turn your favourite traditional treats into adorable, wearable art! In this beginner-friendly 2-hour workshop, you’ll learn how to craft miniature versions of iconic local kueh - from tutu kueh and ang ku kueh to png kueh.<br />Guided step by step, you’ll pick up simple clay techniques to shape, texture, and assemble your creations into accessories you can actually wear or gift.<br /><strong>What you’ll take home:</strong><br />2-3 handmade accessories of your choice - choose from earrings, hair clips, necklaces, bracelets, brooch pins, or keychains - all designed by you! (Quantity is dependent on individual's pace)<br /><br />Perfect for anyone who loves kueh, crafts, or just wants a fun hands-on experience to remember.<br />Drop us an email at <a href=\"mailto:sales@theassembly.space\" rel=\"nofollow\">sales@theassembly.space</a> for other enquiries.</p>",
