        "address": null,
        "coordinates": {
          "lng": 103.85944037199918,
          "lat": 1.2927191446278683
        },
        "category": null,
        "price": null,
        "description": "<p>Join me for a two-hour watercolour workshop to paint Singapore's national flower, the Vanda Miss Joaquim orchid, and learn about its symbolism of resilience and multicultural harmony.<br />Enjoy a relaxing session with tea or coffee as we explore the orchid's history and its representation of strength and unity.<br />Whether you're a beginner or experienced artist, this session offers a perfect blend of creativity and culture.<br /><br />In this workshop you will walk away learning different watercolour techniques and hands on guidance in order to create your very own masterpiece.</p><ul><li><p>All materials are good quality--professional grade paint and paper, and a good quality round 6 Da Vinci brush-- will be provided and yours to take home.</p></li><li><p>Price includes a choice of artisan tea/coffee/beverage </p></li><li><p>The workshop is intended to be a relaxing and calming experience while learning adequate watercolour skills</p></li><li><p>A casual talk on the Singapore's national flower, it's history and cultural significance during the painting session</p></li></ul>",
        "organizer": null,
        "eventUrl": "https://www.sistic.com.sg/event-details/lite_bloomingtogether2",
