        "description": "<p>The Legend of the Monkey King Returns begins with Sun Wukong trapped under the Five Finger Mountain, having lost his powers. The story follows his journey from a stubborn and rebellious monkey to becoming the legendary Great Sage. Through challenges and setbacks, Wukong learns courage, strength, and what it truly means to grow.</p><p>We hope for the Monkey King’s return not only because he is a hero, but because every child can see a bit of themselves in his story - the wish to become braver and stronger.</p><p>This production features elements of Chinese opera, martial arts, Chinese dance, and classic poetry, bringing rich Chinese cultural arts to young audiences in an engaging and accessible way.</p>",
