        "description": "Step on board Fu Ning, Singapore’s remarkable cultural landmark and the world’s largest traditional Chinese wooden sailing vessel, located at the iconic Raffles Marina Lighthouse. Built as part of a UNESCO commitment to preserve intangible cultural heritage, Fu Ning stands as a living tribute to centuries of maritime history and craftsmanship.<br><br>More than just a vessel, Fu Ning offers an immersive cultural and educational experience. Inspired by the legendary treasure ships of the Ming Dynasty led by famed explorer Zheng He, the ship brings to life the stories, skills and innovations that shaped early seafaring journeys across vast oceans.<br><br>As you explore its three beautifully crafted decks, you will discover the intricate artistry of traditional shipbuilding, including the renowned watertight bulkhead technology. Surrounded by warm wooden interiors and authentic design elements, guests are transported into a world where heritage meets refined modern experience.<br><br>Fu Ning is not just a visit - it is a journey through time. An experience that celebrates exploration, resilience and the enduring relationship between people and the sea.",
        "organizer": null,
        "eventUrl": "https://www.catch.sg/Event/Fu-Ning-TourThe-Worlds-Largest-Traditional-Chinese-Wooden-Sailing-Boat-20260317045526",
        "isOnline": false,
