        "category": null,
        "price": null,
        "description": "Step into the world of Sir Stamford Raffles with An Evening at the Lighthouse: Sunset, Dinner & Boat. A guided experience set against the golden coastline of western Singapore.<br>Hosted at Raffles Marina, the evening traces Raffles’ vision of transforming Singapore into a strategic maritime trading port. Through intimate storytelling and conversations at Discovery Pub, uncover how early trade routes, seafaring communities, and colonial ambition shaped the nation’s beginnings.<br>Climb to the top of the lighthouse for exclusive access to its highest point, where sweeping panoramic views and a stunning sunset await. Discover how navigational beacons like this bring to life Sir Stamford Raffles’ vision of Singapore as a key maritime hub. The journey continues board Fu Ning, the world’s largest traditional Chinese wooden sailing boat. Guests will have the opportunity to explore the vessel and capture memorable photos on board as the sun sets over the ocean. The evening concludes with a relaxed waterfront dinner at the marina’s bistro, offering time to unwind and reflect on Singapore’s transformation from a trading outpost to a global port city.<br>This programme offers a rare opportunity to experience heritage, maritime history and dining in one memorable evening by the sea. The tour requires a minimum of 10 participants to proceed. Tickets are sold through Sistic: https://www.sistic.com.sg/events/lite_rafflesheritagesunsettour06 <br><br>•\tRaffles Heritage Storytelling at Discovery Pub - Enjoy light refreshments while discovering the vision of Sir Stamford Raffles, and how Singapore’s early maritime roots shaped its development into a global trading hub.<br>•\tPhoto Opportunities on Board - Capture stunning photos aboard this magnificent vessel.<br>•\tExclusive Visit to Fu Ning - Explore the world’s largest traditional Chinese wooden sailing boat. Learn about its rich maritime heritage craftsmanship inspired by the legendary treasure ships of the famed explorer Zheng He.<br>•\tLighthouse Sunset Experience - Climb to the top of the Raffles Marina Lighthouse and enjoy breathtaking panoramic sunset views over the sea from its highest point.<br>•\tDinner at Bistro - Relax and enjoy a delightful dinner at the marina’s bistro.<br>",
