        "schemaVersion": "1.0",
        "id": "merged:77031bfaca88b05377c40cbead849acdb92e476bc7861bd7e671f698c9425104",
        "title": "Gateway Kids Club - July Storytelling 2026",
        "startDateTime": "Sat, 04 Jul 2026",
        "endDateTime": "Sat, 25 Jul 2026",
        "dateText": "Sat, 04 Jul - Sat, 25 Jul 2026",
        "timeText": null,
        "venue": "Gateway Theatre Dance Studio",
        "venueVerified": true,
        "address": null,
        "coordinates": {
          "lng": 103.8165752490265,
          "lat": 1.2839708536712913
        },
        "category": null,
        "price": null,
        "description": "<p>Together We Can - Stories in July<br />“Our ability to reach unity in diversity will be the beauty and the test of our civilization.” - Mahatma Gandhi<br />This month at Gateway Kids Club,we celebrate teamwork,unity and diversity! Through the stories,kids will learn what it means to accept each other’s differences,and learn how to foster a more inclusive and united society. Join our storytellers for a month of wonder-filled adventures together!<br /><br /><strong><em><u>NEW SESSIONS ADDED WEEKLY</u></em></strong><br />Registration for each storytelling session will open two weeks in advance.</p><ul><li><p>4th July, 10:00 am - The Chief’s Daughter by Storyteller Shien<br />Long ago on Temasek island, boys were chosen to be warriors - but the Chief’s Daughter wants to be one!</p></li><li><p>4th July, 11:00 am - 红头巾· Samsui Women by Storyteller William <strong>·</strong> 故事人伟光<br />红头巾是从中国来新加坡工作的女性。她们戴红色头巾，穿深色衣服，在烈日下辛勤劳作，为新加坡建设作出重要贡献。· The Samsui women were Chinese migrant workers, known for the red headscarves they wore. They laboured tirelessly under the sun, helping to build early Singapore.</p></li><li><p>11th July, 10:00 am - The Great Giggle Festival Rescue by Storyteller Misha<br />When the Giggle Rocket stops working, Zorp the alien sets off on an adventure across Sparkle Galaxy to save the Giggle Festival!</p></li><li><p>11th July, 11:00 am - 彩虹恐龙和我们不一样吗？· Is That Rainbowsaurus So Different From Us? by Storyteller Ying Er <strong>·</strong> 故事人瑛铒<br />小小彩虹恐龙搬进新社区. 其他恐龙都躲着她，因为它们从没见过像她这样的人。她真的那么不一样吗？· The little Rainbowsaurus moves into a new neighbourhood, but the other saures avoid her - they’ve never seen anyone like her! Is she really that different?</p></li><li><p>18th July, 10:00 am - The Proud Butterfly by Storyteller Nat<br />In a beautiful garden, Betty Butterfly learns how to be a gracious neighbour.</p></li><li><p>25th July, 10:00 am - Together, we CAN! by Storyteller Nat<br />Kenny the soda can is excited for a new round of recycling, but finds himself in the wrong bin. Can he and his new friends sort things out in time?</p></li></ul><p> <br />Register now and enjoy these stories for FREE!<br /><br /><u>About Gateway Kids Club</u><br />Gateway Kids Club is a free programme held at Gateway Theatre every Saturday. You can also join the Arts & Crafts session or Free Play activities after the storytelling session! Each month,activities are focused on a different theme.<br /><br />More information on Gateway Kids Club available <a href=\"https://gatewaytheatre.sg/gateway-kids-club/\">here</a>.<br /><br />To stay updated on our programmes,follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/GatewayTheatreSG\">Facebook</a> or <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/Gatewaytheatre_SG/\">Instagram</a>!</p>",
        "organizer": null,
        "eventUrl": "https://www.sistic.com.sg/event-details/lite_gkc202607",
