        "category": null,
        "price": "S$18 - S$58",
        "description": "<p>\"One to Watch\" - International Piano Magazine <br /><br />Malaysian superstar Magdalene Ho makes her debut in Singapore, playing works by Handel, Beethoven, Schubert/Liszt, and Schumann. First-prize winner in the 2023 Clara Haskil International Piano Competition, Magdalene has continued to make waves across the international community for her pianistic virtuosity and depth of maturity. <br /><br />Experience Handel's exuberant Suite No. 5 in E major, famously known for the 'Harmonious Blacksmith' variations that showcase dazzling displays of virtuosity. Beethoven's Sonata Op. 10 No. 3 in D major has been described by his great disciple Czerny as 'grand and significant', and it is indeed the first masterpiece in the cycle of sonatas. <br /><br />Liszt’s tribute to Schubert in the numerous song transcriptions place huge demands on the pianist in both poise and power. Linger and take in the calm beauty of Auf dem Wasser zu singen (To Sing on the Water) and the profound solemnity in Litanei auf das Fest Allerseelen (Litany for the Feast of All Souls). The recital concludes with Schumann's Humoreske, billed as one of his most astonishing, yet overlooked piano works.</p>",
        "organizer": null,
        "eventUrl": "https://www.sistic.com.sg/event-details/magdalene0726",
        "isOnline": false,
